By Bianca Botes, Treasury Partner at Peregrine Treasury Solutions The rand has come under pressure as the first case of the COVID-19 coronavirus has been confirmed in South Africa. The markets are on edge, with many questioning the ability of government to deal with a breakout in SA efficiently. The currency weakened 1.4% during the course of Thursday, trading at R15.46/$, R17.30/€ and R19.99/£. READ: South Africa confirms first case of COVID-19 ­ READ: Here are some tips on staying safe from the #coronavirus READ: The Novel Coronavirus: frequently asked questions